---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = 'Terms of Use';
const description = 'The terms that apply when you use the SHUKE Labs website.';
const contactEmail = 'weizhong2004@gmail.com';
const lastUpdated = '10 July 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Nav />
  <main class="flex-1">
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-6 pb-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink">Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      <div class="prose mt-8">
        <p>
          These terms apply when you use the SHUKE Labs website. By using the site, you agree
          to them.
        </p>

        <h2>Content and ownership</h2>
        <p>
          The content on this site — text, design, logos, and code — belongs to SHUKE Labs Ltd
          unless stated otherwise, and is protected by copyright. You are welcome to read and
          share links to it; please don't republish it as your own.
        </p>

        <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>
          Please don't use this site for anything unlawful or attempt to disrupt, damage, or
          gain unauthorised access to it.
        </p>

        <h2>No warranty</h2>
        <p>
          This site is provided "as is", without warranties of any kind. We do our best to keep
          it accurate and available, but we don't guarantee it is error-free or continuously
          available.
        </p>

        <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the extent permitted by law, SHUKE Labs Ltd is not liable for any loss or damage
          arising from your use of, or inability to use, this site.
        </p>

        <h2 id="terms-of-sale">Terms of sale</h2>
        <p>
          The paid product on this site is a subscription licence to the <strong>My AI Team
          bundle</strong>, sold as an annual plan. The bundle includes My AI Team,
          the Agent Quota Gateway, and Rewind.
        </p>
        <p>
          Payments are processed by <strong>LemonSqueezy</strong>, which is the merchant and
          seller of record for every purchase. This means LemonSqueezy — not SHUKE Labs Ltd —
          handles the payment, charges and remits any applicable sales tax or VAT, and is the
          party you transact with at checkout. SHUKE Labs Ltd is the software licensor: we grant
          you the licence to use the software, while LemonSqueezy handles the sale.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your right to use the software is governed by each product's own licence. My AI Team
          and Rewind are proprietary software, licensed for your use for as long as your
          subscription is active. The Agent Quota Gateway free core is source-available under the
          Business Source License 1.1 (BSL&nbsp;1.1); the bundle subscription covers its
          commercial use alongside the other products.
        </p>
        <p>
          By completing a purchase you agree to these terms of sale, to LemonSqueezy's buyer
          terms shown at checkout, and to the rest of these Terms. These terms of sale are
          governed by the laws of New Zealand (see Governing law below), without affecting any
          mandatory consumer rights in your own country.
        </p>

        <h2 id="refund-policy">Refund policy</h2>
        <p>
          Because LemonSqueezy is the seller of record, refunds are handled under LemonSqueezy's
          refund policy, shown at checkout. We offer a <strong>14-day money-back guarantee</strong>:
          request a refund within 14 days of purchase, for any reason, and we will refund it. As
          a subscription, your plan can also be cancelled at any time to stop future renewals;
          cancelling stops the next charge but does not by itself refund the current period.
        </p>
        <p>
          Nothing here limits rights you have under mandatory law. If you are a consumer in New
          Zealand, the Consumer Guarantees Act 1993 still applies. If you are a consumer in the
          EU or UK, your statutory 14-day cooling-off right still applies — note that where you
          ask for immediate access to digital content, that right may end once delivery begins,
          as permitted by law.
        </p>
        <p>
          To request a refund, use the receipt LemonSqueezy emails you at purchase (it links to
          LemonSqueezy's refund request flow), or email us at
          <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a> and we will help you resolve it
          with LemonSqueezy.
        </p>

        <h2>External links</h2>
        <p>
          This site links to other places — such as GitHub, our blog, and product repositories.
          We are not responsible for the content or practices of third-party sites we link to.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of New Zealand.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms from time to time. When we do, we will revise the
          "Last updated" date above. Questions? Email us at
          <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
